c0 sc0 ls0 ws0">it now does. It is now generally used to denote </div><div class="t m179 x36 h28 y140 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">verbal intercourse between persons, familiar talks, </div><div class="t m17a x36 h28 y141 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">etc., whereas it formerly meant, behavior, con-</div><div class="t m17b x36 h28 y142 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">duct, deportment,&quot; and that is what it means in </div><div class="t m17c x28 h28 y143 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the above passage. The Greek word translated </div><div class="t m17d x36 h28 y144 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">conversation in this text is </div><div class="t m17e x1e h2c y145 ff6 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">trofios. </div><div class="t m17f x70 h28 y146 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and is defined by </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
